    For help with Membership queries\n\n\n\n\n\n\nDonate\nPoppy Shop\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSearch for...\n\n\n\n\n\n\nAll of The Legion\nHow to help \nInfo and advice \nEvents \nRemembrance \nNews and updates \nFind the Legion \nNews \nBranch \nTeaching Remembrance \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPopular today...\n\n\nTeaching Remembrance\n\n\nMembership\n\n\nFields of Remembrance\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nEvery poppy counts\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nDownload your Poppy\nDownload and print our iconic Remembrance Poppy to display at home and show your support for the Armed Forces community\nDonate and download\n\n\n\n\nEvery poppy makes a difference to the lives of our Armed Forces community.The Legion has worked with its members, staff, volunteers and partners to create a range of ways for people to get a poppy and show your support in 2020.Like so many things this year, the Poppy Appeal has to adapt to the threat of Covid-19 and we are asking the public to support us like never before, because every poppy counts.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nFundraise for the Poppy Appeal\nTake a look at the three exciting and easy things you can do to fundraise and support your Poppy Appeal during these difficult times.\nFind out more\n\n\n\n\n\nFundraise for the Poppy Appeal\nTake a look at the three exciting and easy things you can do to fundraise and support your Poppy Appeal during these difficult times.\nFind out more\n\n\n\n\n\n\nBuy a Poppy\nSupport The Royal British Legion by buying your poppies and poppy items online, at the Poppy Shop, this Poppy Appeal.\nShop online\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPoppies in the Post\nDue to Covid-19, many of our volunteers are unable to help at this year\'s Poppy Appeal. We need your help to distribute poppies to your friends and neighbours and ensure we can continue to support our Armed Forces community.\nGet involved\n\n\n\n\n\nPoppies in the Post\nDue to Covid-19, many of our volunteers are unable to help at this year\'s Poppy Appeal. We need your help to distribute poppies to your friends and neighbours and ensure we can continue to support our Armed Forces community.\nGet involved\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nVirtual Poppy Run\nRun, walk or jog any distance, whenever and wherever it suits you. Free to register and your fundraising will support the Poppy Appeal.\nSign up today\n\n\n\n\nOur response to the Covid-19 outbreak\nDuring the coronavirus outbreak our priority remains the safety and well-being of our community.\nRead our full update\n\n\n\nGet involved\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nRemembrance\n\n\nRemembrance\nRemembrance honours those who serve to defend our democratic freedoms. We unite  to remember the service and sacrifice of the Armed Forces community from Britain and the Commonwealth.\n\n                    More about this\n                        \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nHow to help\n\n\nPoppy Appeal\nThe Poppy Appeal is the Royal British Legion\xe2\x80\x99s biggest fundraising campaign held every year in November, during the period of Remembrance. \n\n                    More about this\n                        \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nHow to help\n\n\nOur partners\nCovid-19 has pushed us to make changes in the way we reach people. Our partners are leading on many of these innovations, ensuring as many communities can get involved with this year\'s Poppy Appeal.\n\n                    More about this\n                        \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nHow to help\n\n\nVirtual Field of Remembrance\nAdd your personal tribute to our virtual Field of Remembrance. During these difficult times, it\xe2\x80\x99s important that we still join as a nation to remember the sacrifices made by our Armed Forces\n\n                    More about this\n                        \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nOur team is just a phone call away\nCall us on 0808 802 8080. Lines are open from 8am-8pm every day.\n\n\n\nLatest stories from the Legion\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nNews and updates\n\n\nHow Ethel and Grace struck up a friendship during Coronavirus lockdown\nDuring the coronavirus lockdown we have kept in touch with vulnerable members via a telephone buddy service. \n\n                    More about this\n                        \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nNews and updates\n\n\nPlaying a part during the Covid-19 pandemic\nDuring the Covid-19 pandemic QARANC veteran Lorraine volunteered to go back to her roots in District nursing. \n\n                    More about this\n                        \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nNews and updates\n\n\nSupporting the Army\'s Covid-19 response overseas\nMajor Steve Little was given less than 24 hours to prepare when he was called up to support the Army\xe2\x80\x99s COVID-19 response, leaving behind his family.\n\n                    More about this\n                        \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nNews and updates\n\n\nWW2 veterans on coronavirus\nWW2 veterans on how coronavirus is affecting their lives, and their experiences of coping in the face of adversity.\n\n                    More about this\n                        \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nBack to top\n    \n\n\n\n\nContact\n\nThe Royal British Legion 199 Borough High St LondonSE1 1AA\n\nView on map\n\nGet in touch\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nGet support\n\n\nWho we help\n\n\nCare and independent living\n\n\nPhysical and mental wellbeing\n\n\nFinancial and employment support\n\n\nLocal community connections\n\n\nExpert guidance\n\n\n\n\nGet involved\n\n\nWays to give\n\n\nThings to do\n\n\nPoppy Appeal\n\n\nRemembrance\n\n\n\n\nAbout us\n\n\nWho we are\n\n\nOur history\n\n\nOur family of charities\n\n\nGovernance\n\n\n\n\nQuick links\n\n\nMedia Centre\n\n\nCareers\n\n\nThe Royal Charter\n\n\nOur privacy policy and promise\n\n\nProcurement \n\n\nAffiliates\n\n\nCookie policy\n\n\nModern Slavery Act transparency statement\n\n\nStories\n\n\n\n\n\nGet support\n\n\n\n\nWho we help\n\n\nCare and independent living\n\n\nPhysical and mental wellbeing\n\n\nFinancial and employment support\n\n\nLocal community connections\n\n\nExpert guidance\n\n\n\n\n\